  <compounddef id="SHL" kind="page">
    <compoundname>SHL</compoundname>
    <title>SHL Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">SHL(value,<sp/>count)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Performs a <bold>bitwise shift left</bold> operation on an integer. The first parameter is the value to shift, the second is the number of bit positions.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="SHL_1autotoc_md380">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SHL(1,<sp/>1)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>2</computeroutput> (<computeroutput>0001</computeroutput> → <computeroutput>0010</computeroutput>).</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SHL(3,<sp/>2)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>12</computeroutput> (<computeroutput>0011</computeroutput> → <computeroutput>1100</computeroutput>).</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Multiply<sp/>by<sp/>powers<sp/>of<sp/>two<sp/>using<sp/>SHL</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">n<sp/>=<sp/>7</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SHL(n,<sp/>3)<sp/><sp/><sp/>&apos;<sp/>Same<sp/>as<sp/>7<sp/>*<sp/>8<sp/>=<sp/>56</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="SHL_1autotoc_md382">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Operates on 64-bit integers.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Shifting left by <computeroutput>n</computeroutput> positions is equivalent to multiplying by <computeroutput>2^n</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Bits shifted out on the left are discarded; new bits on the right are filled with zero.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>If the shift count is negative or larger than the bit width, behaviour is undefined.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
